                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote resp="#PA">Initials. Fols. 276–84 addition of 12th century. The note on fol. 284v, 'Presbiter Ofredus et Mancafaxia frater ... hunc fecere librum', is of 13th century. (<ref target="https://catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/000468709">Pächt and Alexander</ref> ii. 21)</decoNote>
                     <decoNote resp="#VD">Large initials (fols. 1<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, 22, 39<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, etc.). Plain red capitals, some slightly ornamental (fols. 135<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, 136, 139<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, 143, 147, 155<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, 184<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, 198<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, etc.); spaces left for large initials (fols. 1<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, 22, 39<hi rend="superscript">v</hi>, etc.).</decoNote>
